                            <comment id="12718843" author="rickhall" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2009 14:08:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12719575" author="rickhall" created="Mon, 15 Jun 2009 14:46:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Modified my fix to only call Class.forName() if the type is an array type, otherwise we could end up with ClassCircularityErrors in some cases; apparently, Class.forName() does its own cycle checking and is more conservative than our approach.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
